&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/avro/pull/237&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/avro/pull/237&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AVRO-2058&quot; title=&quot;ReflectData#isNonStringMap returns true for Utf8 keys&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;AVRO-2058&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;AVRO-2058&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; ReflectData#isNonStringMap returns true for Utf8 keys&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AVRO-2058&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AVRO-2058&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    Since `Utf8` does not have an `Stringable` notation, and is not in `SpecificData#stringableClasses`, `ReflectData#isNonStringMap` returns true. This also causes `ReflectData#isArray` to return true for maps with Utf8 keys, and thus `GenericData#resolveUnion` fails as well. This ultimately causes `ReflectData#write` to fail for schemas that contain a union that contains a map, where the data uses Utf8 for strings.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    This following test case reproduces the issue:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    ```java&lt;br/&gt;
      @Test public void testUnionWithMapWithUtf8Keys() {&lt;br/&gt;
        Schema s = new Schema.Parser().parse&lt;br/&gt;
          (&quot;[\&quot;null\&quot;, &lt;/p&gt;
{\&quot;type\&quot;:\&quot;map\&quot;,\&quot;values\&quot;:\&quot;float\&quot;}
&lt;p&gt;]&quot;);&lt;br/&gt;
        GenericData data = ReflectData.get();&lt;br/&gt;
        HashMap&amp;lt;Utf8,Float&amp;gt; map = new HashMap&amp;lt;Utf8,Float&amp;gt;();&lt;br/&gt;
        map.put(new Utf8(&quot;foo&quot;), 1.0f);&lt;br/&gt;
        assertEquals(1, data.resolveUnion(s, map));&lt;br/&gt;
      }&lt;br/&gt;
    ```&lt;/p&gt;


